		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Western Design Center also offer their toolchain as free to use. It requires registration, though. <br />If you want to mix in C, its compiler/optimizer tool has different files for whether the target is 65c02 or 65816. I assume WDC would be good at this stuff, but i don't know C so i can't comment on how good it is. <br /><br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://www.westerndesigncenter.com/wdc/tools.cfm">http://www.westerndesigncenter.com/wdc/tools.cfm</a><!-- m -->

		

		</td>
